{
  "analysis": "Great! Installation completed, git user created, repository initialized, directories created. Now need to configure SSH password authentication, set up post-receive hook, configure nginx with SSL, generate self-signed certificate, and ensure nginx serves the correct directories. Also need to allow git user to write to deployment directories (or hook runs as git but writes to www-data directories). We'll set up a post-receive hook that checks out the branch to the appropriate directory. Since we have a bare repo, we can use git archive or git worktree. Simpler: use git --work-tree checkout. We'll write hook script in /git/project.git/hooks/post-receive and make executable. Also need to configure nginx to listen on 8443 with SSL, serve /var/www/html/main as root location /, and /var/www/html/dev as location /dev/. Must also disable default nginx site.",
  "plan": "1. Generate self-signed SSL certificate. 2. Create nginx config file for port 8443. 3. Disable default site. 4. Write post-receive hook script. 5. Ensure proper permissions. 6. Restart nginx. 7. Test SSH password authentication (allow password in sshd config). 8. Ensure git user can write to deployment directories via group permissions or sudo. We'll add git to www-data group and set group write permissions.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /etc/nginx\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /etc/nginx/ssl\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 -keyout /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key -out /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt -subj \"/C=US/ST=State/L=City/O=Org/CN=localhost\"\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /etc/nginx/sites-available/git-deploy << 'EOF'\nserver {\n    listen 8443 ssl;\n    server_name localhost;\n\n    ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.crt;\n    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/nginx.key;\n\n    root /var/www/html/main;\n    index index.html;\n\n    location /dev {\n        alias /var/www/html/dev;\n        index index.html;\n    }\n}\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ln -sf /etc/nginx/sites-available/git-deploy /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nginx -t\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "systemctl restart nginx\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "usermod -a -G www-data git\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chmod g+w /var/www/html/main /var/www/html/dev\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chgrp www-data /var/www/html/main /var/www/html/dev\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

{
  "analysis": "Nginx config test passed, but systemctl not available (container likely using other init). Need to restart nginx via service command or directly. Also need to ensure SSH password authentication is enabled. The post-receive hook not yet written. Also need to allow git user to push via SSH with password. We'll configure sshd (if not already). Since we're in a container, SSH may not be installed. Need to install openssh-server and configure. Also need to start ssh service. Let's install openssh-server, configure PasswordAuthentication yes, and start ssh. Then write post-receive hook.",
  "plan": "1. Install openssh-server. 2. Configure sshd to allow password authentication. 3. Start ssh service. 4. Write post-receive hook script. 5. Restart nginx via appropriate command. 6. Test SSH connectivity with git user. 7. Optionally set up git user's authorized_keys but password auth is enough. We'll also ensure git user's shell is /usr/bin/git-shell to restrict to git commands. But we need git user to be able to run the hook script (which will be executed as git). That's fine.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get install -y openssh-server\n",
      "duration": 15.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/#PasswordAuthentication yes/PasswordAuthentication yes/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/PasswordAuthentication no/PasswordAuthentication yes/' /etc/ssh/sshd_config\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo 'PermitRootLogin yes' >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "service ssh start\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /git/project.git/hooks\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > post-receive << 'EOF'\n#!/bin/bash\nwhile read oldrev newrev refname\n do\n   branch=$(basename $refname)\n   if [ \"$branch\" = \"main\" ]; then\n     export GIT_WORK_TREE=/var/www/html/main\n     git checkout -f main\n   elif [ \"$branch\" = \"dev\" ]; then\n     export GIT_WORK_TREE=/var/www/html/dev\n     git checkout -f dev\n   fi\n done\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chmod +x post-receive\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "chown git:git post-receive\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "service nginx restart\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}

